      "writtenOn": "2018-07-31T20:23:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is supposed to represent the alpha of the first frame. You\u0027re right; we don\u0027t yet know what the alpha is of all frames.\n\nThis is another case where we started off with an API that only supported reading the first frame. SkCodec has an SkImageInfo (which I\u0027m in the process of removing) which requires an SkAlphaType. I\u0027ve added FrameInfo\u0027s fAlphaType, which represents the type for that frame, but it\u0027s a little confusing to have one on the SkCodec, too.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 183,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 187,
        "endChar": 28
      },
      "revId": "36facc38703bfce7dcf6e54ba081722571ffb5ec",
