    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c6a9c33f_95e64911",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsGifCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 315,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-07-31T20:23:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If the image is complete and fills the frame, there\u0027s no need to fill to transparent black. But we don\u0027t know at the start whether the image is complete, so in order to avoid showing uninitialized memory, we have to fill either when we discover it\u0027s incomplete (but only the first time), or ahead of time. It\u0027s simpler to fill ahead of time if the image is interlaced (although SkGifCodec repeats rows so that the initial fill may be unnecessary), or if the frame doesn\u0027t fill the image size. (In the latter case, the swizzler doesn\u0027t handle pixels to the left or right of the frame, so for simplicity we do the whole frame before hand.)\n\nThis is all only if the frame is independent, and we handle restoring to the background separately.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 313,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 315,
        "endChar": 36
      },
      "revId": "36facc38703bfce7dcf6e54ba081722571ffb5ec",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4f5b88f6_e5f88428",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsGifCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 320,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-07-31T20:23:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That comment has three cases. Are they all unclear to you? The third case is a little funny, and relates to Chromium\u0027s behavior for a busted image. If there is no color table, Chromium will just draw a completely transparent image, so we clear the pixels to transparent black. An alternative might be to say the image is invalid and not draw it.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 317,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 320,
        "endChar": 26
      },
      "revId": "36facc38703bfce7dcf6e54ba081722571ffb5ec",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c490c8a9_463bae4a",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsGifCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 351,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-07-31T20:23:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "As currently written, SkCodec will have already called rewindIfNeeded. But you\u0027re right that it is overly aggressive.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 350,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 351,
        "endChar": 50
      },
      "revId": "36facc38703bfce7dcf6e54ba081722571ffb5ec",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3b49cb5a_a2ccff2a",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsGifCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 385,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-07-31T20:23:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I would say this should be a break, handled the same way as WUFFS_BASE__STATUS_OK. The FrameInfos/onGetFrameCount should tell us that we\u0027ve reached the end.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 382,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 385,
        "endChar": 45
      },
      "revId": "36facc38703bfce7dcf6e54ba081722571ffb5ec",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "335d5d13_0606d337",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsGifCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 415,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-07-31T20:23:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is kind of confusing. We don\u0027t use it if we successfully decoded the entire image. Let\u0027s say you have a 10 pixel high image (both the frame and the image). If you only decoded the first 3 rows, you\u0027d set this to 3, and then SkCodec (or the client of incrementalDecode()) would zero-initialize the remaining 7 (unless the memory was already zero-initialized).\n\nNow let\u0027s say that the image is still 10 pixels high, but the frame is from row 5 to 9. If you only decoded 3 rows, but you initialized the first 5, you could return 8, and the caller would zero-initialize the final 2. In SkGifCodec, we just zero-initialize all 10 rows ahead of time (as you do here) and return the height of the image, so the caller knows it doesn\u0027t need to do anything. (To match that behavior, I think you\u0027d want to return fPixelBuffer.height()?) That\u0027s wasted work, and it\u0027s possible there\u0027s a better way to do it, but I haven\u0027t investigated it.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 415,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 415,
        "endChar": 78
      },
      "revId": "36facc38703bfce7dcf6e54ba081722571ffb5ec",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2da2fdbf_5a030328",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsGifCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 430,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-07-31T20:23:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Given the existing architecture, I think that would make more sense. That would both rewind the stream and call onRewind.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 429,
        "startChar": 46,
        "endLine": 430,
        "endChar": 54
      },
      "revId": "36facc38703bfce7dcf6e54ba081722571ffb5ec",
