      },
      "lineNbr": 453,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-07-31T20:23:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I said this elsewhere, but I *thought* the fact that it has move constructors means it can be used directly in a vector. But if I\u0027m wrong, I don\u0027t have a problem of making it not SkNoncopyable.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 450,
